net.hudup.core.data

Class InterchangeAttributeMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.data.InterchangeAttributeMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, TextParsable

    public class InterchangeAttributeMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, Cloneable, TextParsable
    This class includes both internal record represented by InternalRecord class and external record represented by ExternalRecord class. As a convention, it is called interchanged attribute map for importing data (represented by internal attribute) from other database (represented by external attribute). Note, internal record represents a single-value record of a unit in framework database. External record represents an single-value record stored in other database (different from the framework database).
    There is a special unit (having name "hdp_attribute_map", for example) for storing many interchanged attribute maps; Unit represents a CSV file, database table, Excel sheet, etc. Unit is used to store object such as user profile, item profile, rating matrix, etc.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
